# 1. How has crop production yield changed from 1997 to 2015?
plt.plot(d.groupby("Crop_Year")["Production"].sum()/100000)
plt.title("crop production yield changed from 1997 to 2015")
plt.ylabel("Production in lakhs")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.show()

Ans - So, the above line graph for production year shows that overall there was a upward trend in prouction from 1997 to 2011 but took a high leap down afterwards with a point rise only in year 2013 & 2014.

In [ ]:
# 2. Over time, what are the major production trends been across the states?

n = d["State_Name"].nunique()
s = d["State_Name"].unique()

for i in range(0,n):
    plt.subplots(1,1)
    plt.plot(d[d["State_Name"]==s[i]].groupby("Crop_Year")["Production"].sum()/1000)
    plt.title(s[i])
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Production in 1,000s")
    plt.show()

Ans - So, the above line graphs for production in various states over the year shows that some states have downward trend whereas some have upward or sideways.

In [ ]:
# 3. Are there any patterns that can be observed between total crop production and value of production every year?
# How has value of production, which in some sense could be tied to demand, changed every year?

n = d["Crop"].nunique()
s = d["Crop"].unique()

for i in range(0,n):
    plt.subplots(1,1)
    plt.scatter(d[d["Crop"]==s[i]].groupby("Crop_Year")["Production"].sum()/1000,d[d["Crop"]==s[i]].groupby("Crop_Year")["Area"].sum()/1000)
    plt.title(s[i])
    plt.xlabel("Production in 1,000s")
    plt.ylabel("Area in 1,000s")
    plt.show()

Ans - So, It can be observed from above point plots that correlation between Area & Production in various states over various years is high.

So, it can be observed that production of any crop will increase on increasing the area and visa-versa.

# 3. Alternative

n = d["Crop"].nunique()
s = d["Crop"].unique()

for i in range(0,n):
    p = d[d["Crop"]==s[i]].groupby("Crop_Year")["Production"].sum()/1000
    a = d[d["Crop"]==s[i]].groupby("Crop_Year")["Area"].sum()/1000
    print(s[i])
    plt.subplots(1,1)
    sns.heatmap((pd.merge(p,a,right_index = True,left_index = True)).corr())
    plt.show()

#Pair plot between sum of area & production over the years

a = d.groupby("Crop_Year")["Area"].sum()/1000
sns.pairplot((pd.merge(p,a,right_index = True,left_index = True)))
